# Ignore-file for the root Go `Dockerfile`. BuildKit resolves a Dockerfile-adjacent
# <dockerfile>.dockerignore ahead of the root .dockerignore, so this file governs the
# Go image context while the SPA builds (frontend/<app>/Dockerfile) keep using the
# root .dockerignore. KEEP go.mod, go.sum, cmd/**, internal/** — everything the Go
# build needs; exclude everything else to keep the context small and the cache stable.

# Frontend / Node — never part of a Go image
node_modules
**/node_modules
frontend
packages
package.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
pnpm-workspace.yaml
Caddyfile
**/dist
**/.vite
**/.verify

# VCS / CI / tooling / docs
.git
.github
.claude
backlog
docs
e2e
*.md

# DB tooling — not needed to compile a service binary. `migrations/` and
# `db/bootstrap.sql` / `db/seed.dev.sql` are the exceptions (M2-12, M4-21-03): the
# gateway embeds migrations/*.sql AND those two db/*.sql files via go:embed
# (migrations.md §2; internal/platform/db.Bootstrap/.Seed), so they MUST be in the
# Go build context or the gateway image fails to compile. It is a shared
# Dockerfile, so migrations/ and the two db/*.sql files land in every service's
# context; the seven context services simply never import them.
db
!db/bootstrap.sql
!db/seed.dev.sql
!db/embed.go
Makefile
docker-compose.yml

# Docker / env / editor / OS
Dockerfile
Dockerfile.dockerignore
.dockerignore
.env
.env.*
**/.env
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
